House Resolution 53
By: Representative Berry of the 56th
A RESOLUTION
1 Honoring the life and memory of Emily L. Milner; and for other purposes.
2 WHEREAS, the State of Georgia mourns the loss of one of its most distinguished citizens
3 with the passing of Emily L. Milner on December 17, 2024; and
4 WHEREAS, Emily L. Milner was born on January 18, 1917, and this year represents the
5 108th anniversary of her birth; and
6 WHEREAS, a woman of deep and abiding faith, Emily L. Milner was an active member of
7 the Shrine of the Immaculate Conception in Atlanta; and
8 WHEREAS, affectionately know as Miss Emily by her congregation, she held her faith close
9 to her heart, devoted her time to praying the rosary, faithfully attended mass, and proudly
10 held the title of longest-living alumna of Our Lady of Lourdes School; and
11 WHEREAS, she gave inspiration to many through her high ideals, morals, and deep concern
12 for her fellow citizens, and the devotion, patience, and understanding she demonstrated to
13 her family and friends were admired by others; and
