14 WHEREAS, she was a person of magnanimous strengths with an unimpeachable reputation
15 for integrity, intelligence, fairness, and kindness, and by the example she made of her life,
16 she made this world a better place in which to live; and
17 WHEREAS, a compassionate and generous woman, Emily L. Milner will long be
18 remembered for her love of Christ, her family, and her community and will be missed by all
19 who had the great fortune of knowing her.
20 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES that
21 the members of this body join in honoring the life and memory of Emily L. Milner and
22 express their deepest and most sincere regret at her passing.
23 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Clerk of the House of Representatives is authorized
24 and directed to make an appropriate copy of this resolution available for distribution to the
25 family of Emily L. Milner.
